N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 ยง 441.288 - Relative value unit

State Regulations

Index number assigned to various procedures based upon
the relative amount of labor, supplies and capital needed to perform the
procedure. The unit value represents the cost of performing a service relative
to some other service which is used as a base, i.e., has a unit value of
one. Notes
